actions.text: Referred to House Committee on Foreign Affairs.
Reported to House from the Committee on Foreign Affairs, H. Rept. 93-1020.
Referred to Senate Committee on Commerce.
Reported to Senate from the Committee on Commerce with amendment, S. Rept. 93-893.

official_title: An Act to amend the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries Act of 1950 to permit U. S. participation in international enforcement of fish conservation in additional geographic areas, pursuant to the International Convention for the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries 1949, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Permits, under the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries Act of 1950, United States participation in international enforcement of fish conservation in geographic areas specified by the International Commission for the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries, pursuant to the International Convention for the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries.
